1
00:00:18,940 --> 00:00:23,880
ظآزOnly after bloom comes fruitظآز

2
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:29,260
ظآزWho says glory must fade to the pastظآز

3
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,010
ظآزOnly through thunder
do you reach the cloudsظآز

4
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:43,120
ظآزWho made you the crown of every peakظآز

5
00:00:44,650 --> 00:00:47,930
ظآزI stand at the center of the stageظآز

6
00:00:47,930 --> 00:00:51,000
ظآزMy shadow is pinned against the wallظآز

7
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:56,660
ظآزFacing the light earns every medalظآز

8
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:00,880
ظآزLittle birds,
save your needless peckingظآز

9
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,160
ظآزThe open sky rises highظآز

10
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:09,830
ظآزWhen night falls,
the moon begins to shineظآز

11
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,860
ظآزI stand in the heart of these landsظآز

12
00:01:13,860 --> 00:01:17,220
ظآزMy shadow bears no crown or robeظآز

13
00:01:17,630 --> 00:01:23,300
ظآزThen I know truth needs no disguiseظآز

14
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:26,960
ظآزThe green hills see me as I amظآز

15
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,290
ظآزLike dew, lightning,
and moon on the riverظآز

16
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:34,730
ظآزShowing me exactly who I amظآز

17
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:35,980
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 5=

19
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:48,680
How is it? Happy now?

20
00:01:49,080 --> 00:01:49,920
Yeah.

21
00:01:55,740 --> 00:02:00,120
(Department Store)

22
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:00,960
Come on, get down.

23
00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:04,480
(Yi Qing'e got into the trainee class.)

24
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:08,120
(Hu Sanyuan and Hua Caixiang
were the happiest of all.)

25
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,880
(Their little shepherd girl)

26
00:02:10,040 --> 00:02:11,800
(got to eat commodity grain.)

27
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:14,760
(She didn't know)

28
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:16,000
(what that meant,)

29
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:20,760
(but not everyone could get it.)

30
00:02:28,380 --> 00:02:32,260
(Shoes and Hats)

31
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:46,880
Let's go.

32
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:53,280
(Photos, Developed)

33
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,160
Three,

34
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:55,600
two,

35
00:02:56,160 --> 00:02:57,000
one.

36
00:02:58,480 --> 00:02:59,320
All done.

37
00:02:59,966 --> 00:03:00,840
She didn't even smile.

38
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,720
This kid just doesn't smile.

39
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,560
Right, right. Okay, come on.

40
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,200
Alright, we're done here.

41
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:07,560
You don't smile.

42
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:08,960
When can we get the photos?

43
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:09,800
Tomorrow.

44
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:10,680
Here's my suggestion.

45
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:12,800
The three of you should

46
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:14,360
take a family photo together.

47
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:17,160
Sir, what are you saying?

48
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:18,000
Sure.

49
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:21,360
Sure what? Why stir this up?

50
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:23,160
The kid got in. Mark the moment.

51
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:24,600
I taught that kid myself.

52
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:26,240
You two take the photo.

53
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:27,080
Mark the moment.

54
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,040
Come here.

55
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:39,520
Wait a second.

56
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:42,120
What is it now?

57
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:43,720
Hold this.

58
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:47,040
We're taking a photo.

59
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:48,560
Why are you acting weird?

60
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,440
The kid got in. Let's celebrate.

61
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:52,240
Let's take a proud family photo.

62
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:54,560
It looks like you've done this before.

63
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:56,080
Look over here.

64
00:03:57,920 --> 00:03:58,920
Give me a little smile.

65
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:00,960
Scoot a little closer together.

66
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:04,960
Okay, three, two, one.

67
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:13,520
ظآزThe red star is twinklingظآز

68
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:16,920
ظآزThe journeyظآز

69
00:04:18,840 --> 00:04:20,080
Zhou Ren Hui Fu (Classical Qinqiang opera).

70
00:04:20,840 --> 00:04:22,720
What are you saying? Are you dreaming?

71
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:28,320
Time for the opera.

72
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:30,240
I can't do it today.

73
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,246
(Troupe)
Another day.

74
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,520
You clueless blockhead.

75
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,360
Well.

76
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:40,240
It's from Shanghai.

77
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,560
- Here.
- I see.

78
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:42,640
Shanghai.

79
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:43,680
Zhang Guangrong?

80
00:04:45,413 --> 00:04:46,720
What brings you back so suddenly?

81
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:47,560
Caixiang,

82
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:49,840
I wanted to surprise you.

83
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:51,920
Where have you been?

84
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:53,320
Whose kid is this?

85
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,406
Hu Sanyuan's niece.

86
00:04:55,417 --> 00:04:56,609
She's studying opera with me.

87
00:04:56,620 --> 00:04:57,480
Sanyuan.

88
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:58,340
You're back.

89
00:04:58,340 --> 00:04:59,180
I'm back.

90
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:04,446
When did you get back?

91
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:05,560
Just now.

92
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:10,673
Go inside with your uncle.

93
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,440
Okay, okay.

94
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:14,760
Come on inside.

95
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:16,480
Come by later for a drink.

96
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:17,600
Okay, okay.

97
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:20,560
Okay, we're off.

98
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,440
In this yard...

99
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:31,840
You're drenched in sweat.

100
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:35,000
Have you eaten yet?

101
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:37,360
Yeah, at the cafeteria.

102
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:38,880
I'll get you some water.

103
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:40,480
I already had some.

104
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:43,120
I had some with your troupe.

105
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:45,360
There's no water left. I'll get some.

106
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:47,720
Don't go. I'm not thirsty.

107
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,800
But I've been walking and sweating too.

108
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,080
I'm thirsty.

109
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:56,400
I'll go.

110
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,560
Okay, you go ahead. Go on.

111
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,240
Laidi,

112
00:06:37,960 --> 00:06:39,680
you can't sleep with me tonight.

113
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:51,240
Anything wrong?

114
00:06:54,760 --> 00:06:55,720
I want to tell him

115
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:57,200
about the divorce.

116
00:06:58,320 --> 00:06:59,200
You can't tell him.

117
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:00,400
Why?

118
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:02,040
No reason.

119
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:05,160
You jerk.

120
00:07:16,780 --> 00:07:17,640
Where are you off to?

121
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:19,000
I'm getting the kid some candy.

122
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:26,560
What's your name?

123
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:29,920
Here, have some candy.

124
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:32,320
Go on, take it.

125
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:35,360
Say thanks to Uncle.

126
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,200
Here, take it.

127
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:39,800
How did I become her uncle?

128
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:43,040
She calls Hua Caixiang Aunt.

129
00:07:45,280 --> 00:07:46,720
Go on, go play with Bayi.

130
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:50,880
Your niece is studying opera
with Caixiang?

131
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:53,160
To let her be a trainee,

132
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:55,960
I had Hua Caixiang coach her
for the exam.

133
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:57,680
That's a good thing.

134
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,100
Is the water not boiling?

135
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:10,480
It just started boiling.

136
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:11,340
Then hurry up.

137
00:08:11,340 --> 00:08:12,400
I'll help. How many scoops?

138
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,080
Two.

139
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:14,920
Okay.

140
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:18,240
Zhang Guangrong is back.

141
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:19,900
Why are you getting the water?

142
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:23,080
Zhang Guangrong

143
00:08:23,080 --> 00:08:24,120
is not good enough.

144
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,080
That's true.

145
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:47,520
How have you been?

146
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:48,960
Same as always.

147
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:51,640
Still just feeding yourself?

148
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,640
I'm feeding two now.

149
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:55,080
Who's the other one?

150
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:56,400
My niece.

151
00:08:58,560 --> 00:08:59,800
Sanyuan, have a seat.

152
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:00,840
I'll show you.

153
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:02,440
Let me show you.

154
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:05,920
Take a look.

155
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:10,800
Who are these?

156
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:13,040
Two female workers from our factory.

157
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:14,600
They're into the arts.

158
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:16,520
The Workers' Propaganda Team members.

159
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:18,520
Unmarried young women.

160
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,960
You're matchmaking for me.

161
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:24,326
There are lots of women at our factory.

162
00:09:24,933 --> 00:09:25,993
These two are good-looking.

163
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,966
They've got good backgrounds and hearts.

164
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:29,800
And they both love the arts.

165
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:31,600
Then it hit me.

166
00:09:31,880 --> 00:09:33,200
Isn't Sanyuan still single?

167
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:35,840
So?

168
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:37,680
Do you like either one?

169
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:40,320
Honestly, both are appealing.

170
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,080
What is it?

171
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:44,960
Your wedding candy?

172
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:47,720
I get it now.

173
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,819
It's from Hua Caixiang's husband, right?

174
00:09:50,520 --> 00:09:51,960
He brings candy every time he's back.

175
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:54,680
Come on, follow me.

176
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:06,040
All my treasures are in here.

177
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:07,560
Look.

178
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:08,560
Look.

179
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,160
Look.

180
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:12,160
This whole box is my treasure.

181
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:14,000
You can put your candy in too.

182
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,440
Don't worry. I won't take yours.

183
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:20,560
Count them.

184
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:24,840
Five pieces.

185
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:26,360
Here, put them in. Come on.

186
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:29,640
Okay.

187
00:10:30,680 --> 00:10:32,080
Don't let anyone know this secret.

188
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:33,280
Got it?

189
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:39,720
Tonight, I'll show you another secret.

190
00:11:09,120 --> 00:11:09,960
Come on.

191
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:24,120
What's this?

192
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:28,960
They say this is the Four Olds.

193
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:33,680
You look good.

194
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,680
Just like people in old paintings.

195
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:46,360
What's this?

196
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:48,880
Candy?

197
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:52,840
The smell is so strong.

198
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:10,920
I had someone get this

199
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:13,200
for you from Shanghai. It's Dacron.

200
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,680
The latest style in Shanghai.

201
00:13:14,680 --> 00:13:15,800
Here, try it on.

202
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:17,160
I think this color...

203
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:18,120
There's another one

204
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:19,360
in this color.

205
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,220
I think

206
00:13:20,220 --> 00:13:21,100
it looks

207
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:22,280
pretty good.

208
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:23,840
What do you think?

209
00:13:28,360 --> 00:13:29,760
Try it on and see if it fits.

210
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:31,520
No need.

211
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:33,406
If it doesn't fit, I can't return it.

212
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:40,200
What's wrong?

213
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:41,960
Nothing's wrong.

214
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:43,660
You're not happy with my return?

215
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,320
I am happy.

216
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:48,120
I can't tell.

217
00:13:50,240 --> 00:13:51,720
Should I call out the orchestra

218
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:52,800
and sing for you?

219
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:55,160
It's too late.

220
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:56,800
We shouldn't wake everyone up.

221
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:06,840
I know all about your situation.

222
00:14:09,560 --> 00:14:10,400
What situation?

223
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:12,240
The anonymous letter.

224
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:14,680
Huang Zhengjing wrote and told me.

225
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:18,680
What else did he tell you?

226
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:21,920
Is there anything else?

227
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:27,760
I don't want to talk about that.

228
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:29,440
It kills the mood.

229
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:32,280
Anything on your mind?

230
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:35,040
Nothing.

231
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:37,040
How long are you staying?

232
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:39,320
It's hard to say.

233
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:42,960
The factory may call me back anytime.

234
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:51,200
The Factory Revolutionary Committee
talked to me.

235
00:14:52,080 --> 00:14:54,040
They're focusing on production now.

236
00:14:54,960 --> 00:14:56,120
If nothing goes wrong,

237
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:57,553
I may be promoted to Deputy Director

238
00:14:57,680 --> 00:14:59,233
of the Factory Revolutionary Committee.

239
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:00,600
That's great news.

240
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,040
Congrats to you.

241
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:04,960
What's so great about it?

242
00:15:05,560 --> 00:15:06,440
If I really become

243
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:07,840
the Deputy Director,

244
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:10,040
we'll have even less time together.

245
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:19,726
You should transfer over.

246
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:22,680
We can't live apart forever.

247
00:15:24,040 --> 00:15:24,880
I'm not going.

248
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:29,160
Why?

249
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:31,720
I want to perform in opera.

250
00:15:32,760 --> 00:15:34,200
Is that the only reason?

251
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:38,120
What are you getting at?

252
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:39,880
I mean,

253
00:15:40,160 --> 00:15:41,240
it's time we had a baby.

254
00:15:42,560 --> 00:15:43,400
Let's have a child.

255
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:06,240
I'm going to wash up.

256
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:58,480
This dirt platform is my stage.

257
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:00,400
So, I've performed

258
00:17:00,640 --> 00:17:01,680
in opera on stage.

259
00:17:03,280 --> 00:17:04,320
Come on, do a bit too.

260
00:17:05,480 --> 00:17:06,800
What are you spacing out for?

261
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:09,920
Missing Jiuyangou again?

262
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:14,520
I may never make it back again.

263
00:17:16,320 --> 00:17:18,680
Life really isn't fair.

264
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:21,360
I dream of performing in opera.

265
00:17:22,120 --> 00:17:24,200
How come I don't have an uncle
like yours?

266
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:26,960
My two uncles are both back
in our hometown.

267
00:17:27,360 --> 00:17:29,040
One of them asks my family for money

268
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:30,320
and never pays it back.

269
00:17:30,766 --> 00:17:32,539
The other one is five years younger
than me.

270
00:17:32,550 --> 00:17:34,749
I even have to clean him up
after he relieves himself.

271
00:17:34,760 --> 00:17:35,640
You're so lucky

272
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:37,280
to have your uncle.

273
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:40,480
I'm scared of him.

274
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:42,280
Why?

275
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:43,960
I can't explain it.

276
00:17:44,560 --> 00:17:46,560
You catch snakes and take on Er Laizi.

277
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:48,160
Why be scared of your uncle?

278
00:17:48,480 --> 00:17:50,160
I just have a bad feeling,

279
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:52,560
as if something's about to happen.

280
00:17:53,360 --> 00:17:55,160
With me here, what could happen?

281
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:56,000
Watch this.

282
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:58,160
Cut the nonsense.

283
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:59,000
So what?

284
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:00,200
So what?

285
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:01,600
What are you going to do?

286
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:02,840
What can you do?

287
00:18:42,800 --> 00:18:45,000
What's going on? I've waited forever.

288
00:18:45,440 --> 00:18:46,840
Something came up and held me back.

289
00:18:47,240 --> 00:18:48,320
Did you bolt the door?

290
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:49,160
Yeah, I did.

291
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:50,100
- Go.
- Go.

292
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:56,400
Turn on the light.

293
00:19:13,980 --> 00:19:21,380
ظآزDon't act wild hereظآز

294
00:19:21,380 --> 00:19:26,900
ظآزYou killed my father;
how could I let goظآز

295
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:31,740
ظآزI shouldn't haveظآز

296
00:19:32,020 --> 00:19:36,980
ظآزI should've only killed traitorsظآز

297
00:19:36,980 --> 00:19:39,160
ظآزChasing the throneظآز

298
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:42,040
(The night Zhang Guangrong came back,)

299
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:45,240
(the poolside was no longer lively.)

300
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:50,320
(The yard was as quiet
as a night in Jiuyangou.)

301
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:54,560
(It felt like everyone was waiting
for something to happen.)

302
00:19:54,720 --> 00:19:57,080
(But nothing happened that night.)

303
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:59,240
(Maybe something did,)

304
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:01,280
(but no one knew.)

305
00:20:03,060 --> 00:20:07,100
ظآزOpen up the record of meritظآز

306
00:20:07,100 --> 00:20:11,420
ظآزSee what your father has doneظآز

307
00:20:11,420 --> 00:20:15,300
ظآزMy father was praised for his deedsظآز

308
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:19,380
ظآزYet his name is not on the recordظآز

309
00:20:19,380 --> 00:20:20,660
ظآزThe emperor rules allظآز

310
00:20:20,780 --> 00:20:22,100
ظآزIt's ruled half by his courtظآز

311
00:20:22,100 --> 00:20:23,300
ظآزThis realm belongs to meظآز

312
00:20:23,300 --> 00:20:24,540
ظآزNo need to consult youظآز

313
00:20:24,540 --> 00:20:25,700
ظآزYour realm was builtظآز

314
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:27,100
ظآزBy our familiesظآز

315
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:28,260
ظآزDo you want the throneظآز

316
00:20:28,260 --> 00:20:29,740
ظآزNo, but I won't give it awayظآز

317
00:20:29,740 --> 00:20:30,900
ظآزI have to give it to himظآز

318
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:32,220
ظآزNo, you truly can'tظآز

319
00:20:32,220 --> 00:20:33,580
ظآزYou were given such a high postظآز

320
00:20:33,580 --> 00:20:34,820
ظآزNow, you ignore meظآز

321
00:20:34,820 --> 00:20:36,100
ظآزI earned my postظآز

322
00:20:36,100 --> 00:20:37,340
ظآزNot your benevolenceظآز

323
00:20:37,340 --> 00:20:38,620
ظآزYou should've been beheadedظآز

324
00:20:38,620 --> 00:20:39,940
ظآزYou can't behead meظآز

325
00:20:39,940 --> 00:20:41,180
ظآزI must behead youظآز

326
00:20:41,180 --> 00:20:42,580
ظآزNo, you truly can'tظآز

327
00:20:42,580 --> 00:20:43,780
ظآزI'll have the guardsظآز

328
00:20:43,780 --> 00:20:48,340
ظآزHang your head at the Meridian Gateظآز

329
00:20:54,280 --> 00:20:55,120
Director.

330
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:16,880
Director, look.

331
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:32,480
Deputy Director Zhu, what's going on?

332
00:21:33,320 --> 00:21:35,320
Making room for the trainees.

333
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:50,600
What about this old thing?

334
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:54,760
Worry about what happens to you first.

335
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,040
Qiu Cunyi,

336
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:04,440
do you think those emperors, nobles,

337
00:22:04,440 --> 00:22:06,400
queens, consorts, lords, and ladies

338
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:07,920
can still make it onto the stage?

339
00:22:07,920 --> 00:22:09,720
That's absolutely impossible.

340
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:12,100
These weren't handled in time,

341
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:13,480
so they were put here.

342
00:22:16,080 --> 00:22:18,190
It seems some troublemakers

343
00:22:18,190 --> 00:22:19,090
just won't give up

344
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:22,230
on performing on the stage.

345
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:23,800
Director Huang,

346
00:22:24,640 --> 00:22:27,640
I swear. I'll burn it all today.

347
00:22:32,280 --> 00:22:33,840
Hurry up. Burn it all now.

348
00:23:00,280 --> 00:23:01,120
Director Huang.

349
00:23:01,420 --> 00:23:02,280
Guangrong.

350
00:23:02,280 --> 00:23:03,120
Director Huang.

351
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:05,040
When did you get back?

352
00:23:05,040 --> 00:23:06,000
Last night.

353
00:23:06,280 --> 00:23:07,400
Sit, sit. Come on.

354
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:08,800
Perfect timing.

355
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:10,200
Try some tea from my hometown.

356
00:23:10,280 --> 00:23:12,080
First pick of the season. So fresh.

357
00:23:12,080 --> 00:23:13,200
I got this for you.

358
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:14,680
The latest Shanghai-brand watch.

359
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:19,440
Wow, you really got one.

360
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:22,520
Shanghai watches are in high demand.

361
00:23:22,520 --> 00:23:23,800
They're really hard to buy.

362
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:26,720
Working in a big city is different.

363
00:23:27,680 --> 00:23:29,280
We're at the same rank,

364
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:31,440
but I still need your help for a watch.

365
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:33,240
Honestly,

366
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:34,800
the army is better.

367
00:23:35,240 --> 00:23:36,820
The troupe is way too loose.

368
00:23:36,820 --> 00:23:37,680
I don't like it.

369
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:39,040
You're right.

370
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:40,600
Guangrong,

371
00:23:40,760 --> 00:23:42,880
you got lucky with that assignment.

372
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:44,440
As for my troupe,

373
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:46,240
that whole bunch is

374
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:47,720
just sloppy

375
00:23:48,160 --> 00:23:49,160
and undisciplined,

376
00:23:49,480 --> 00:23:50,880
with no order at all.

377
00:23:51,280 --> 00:23:53,520
This job has me all worked up.

378
00:23:54,720 --> 00:23:56,000
It's an arts unit, after all.

379
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:57,080
They're strong-willed.

380
00:23:58,080 --> 00:23:58,920
Right.

381
00:23:59,320 --> 00:24:01,320
If they're a bit carefree
and strong-willed

382
00:24:01,320 --> 00:24:03,720
in the troupe, I get that.

383
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:06,120
What I can't accept most is

384
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:07,320
the relationships...

385
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:09,120
It'll blow up.

386
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:10,600
Is that true?

387
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:11,440
Exactly.

388
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:12,440
Stop talking.

389
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:14,920
The relationships are a real mess.

390
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:16,640
Listen.

391
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:18,880
That's moral decay.

392
00:24:18,880 --> 00:24:20,880
It's a matter of conduct.

393
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:28,280
The rumors about your wife
and Hu Sanyuan

394
00:24:28,680 --> 00:24:29,560
are getting worse.

395
00:24:30,120 --> 00:24:30,960
They're everywhere.

396
00:24:31,320 --> 00:24:32,280
I can't contain it now.

397
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:35,240
Guangrong, I did all I could.

398
00:24:35,720 --> 00:24:36,800
I really did all I could.

399
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:41,240
To protect the name of Hua Caixiang
as the lead

400
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:43,280
and to protect your reputation,

401
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:44,720
I had no choice

402
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:46,560
but to talk with Hua Caixiang.

403
00:24:47,480 --> 00:24:50,040
I had to help her see what was at stake.

404
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:52,520
I had to let her see it.

405
00:24:53,080 --> 00:24:54,080
But look what happened.

406
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:57,360
Someone with bad intent used me.

407
00:24:57,920 --> 00:24:59,880
They sent an anonymous letter to my home

408
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:01,200
and reported me.

409
00:25:02,120 --> 00:25:03,680
Do you think I'd do something like that?

410
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:05,200
Look at the bond between us.

411
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:07,040
Isn't this just slander?

412
00:25:07,720 --> 00:25:09,920
This has left me completely overwhelmed.

413
00:25:09,920 --> 00:25:11,320
I've been made a total mess.

414
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:13,120
I understand.

415
00:25:13,840 --> 00:25:15,680
I don't need your understanding,
Guangrong.

416
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:18,400
The point is, this is your issue.

417
00:25:19,040 --> 00:25:19,960
You need

418
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:21,480
to get Hua Caixiang to see

419
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:23,600
how serious this is.

420
00:25:25,320 --> 00:25:26,160
Of course,

421
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:29,520
Comrade Hua Caixiang means well,

422
00:25:29,840 --> 00:25:31,040
and she's good at her job.

423
00:25:31,560 --> 00:25:32,760
Maybe this rumor

424
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:34,160
is just hearsay.

425
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:36,840
But we still need to stay alert.

426
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:38,720
You got back just in time.

427
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:41,160
This time, talk to her soon.

428
00:25:41,680 --> 00:25:42,720
Talk it through.

429
00:25:43,280 --> 00:25:44,120
Really get into it.

430
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:46,240
Make her understand

431
00:25:46,560 --> 00:25:48,720
whether at work or in daily life,

432
00:25:49,160 --> 00:25:51,280
no matter how close colleagues are,

433
00:25:51,280 --> 00:25:53,040
men and women are still different.

434
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:55,360
There should still be some distance.

435
00:25:56,160 --> 00:25:57,560
What's this about, Zhou?

436
00:25:57,760 --> 00:25:59,200
I'm still on the clock here.

437
00:25:59,520 --> 00:26:00,800
Let Qiu explain it to you.

438
00:26:04,360 --> 00:26:05,200
What's going on?

439
00:26:12,360 --> 00:26:14,160
Why did you call me over and go quiet?

440
00:26:14,920 --> 00:26:16,200
We'll lose the coat trunk.

441
00:26:20,040 --> 00:26:20,880
Why?

442
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:23,040
Huang Zhengjing found out.

443
00:26:24,280 --> 00:26:26,080
I told you this long ago.

444
00:26:26,240 --> 00:26:27,400
That place wasn't secure.

445
00:26:27,400 --> 00:26:29,080
I told you to split it up.

446
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:30,760
What good are you, huh?

447
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:32,320
That was useless talk from you.

448
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:35,080
There are over a dozen big trunks.

449
00:26:35,760 --> 00:26:38,640
Over a hundred opera costumes
and opera headwear are to be split up.

450
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:40,933
Anyone can talk big and act smart.

451
00:26:40,944 --> 00:26:42,040
You're the one talking big.

452
00:26:42,040 --> 00:26:42,880
You are!

453
00:26:43,080 --> 00:26:44,120
You are!

454
00:26:44,480 --> 00:26:45,640
Enough, enough.

455
00:26:46,280 --> 00:26:47,360
We're out of time here.

456
00:26:47,360 --> 00:26:48,840
Hurry up and think of something.

457
00:26:48,840 --> 00:26:49,680
What can we do?

458
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:52,040
Burn them.

459
00:26:53,440 --> 00:26:54,280
Burn them?

460
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:56,080
I'll burn you first.

461
00:26:57,280 --> 00:26:58,720
Don't make this hard for him.

462
00:26:59,320 --> 00:27:00,880
Old ideas, old culture,

463
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:02,400
old customs, and old habits.

464
00:27:03,680 --> 00:27:04,800
We're old folks,

465
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:06,190
not far from the Four Olds.

466
00:27:06,190 --> 00:27:07,640
If we don't burn these clothes,

467
00:27:07,920 --> 00:27:09,720
we'll be the ones burned next.

468
00:27:10,280 --> 00:27:12,760
Back then, we wore them to survive.

469
00:27:13,280 --> 00:27:15,320
Now, we burn them to stay alive.

470
00:27:15,840 --> 00:27:17,000
There's nothing to discuss.

471
00:27:17,320 --> 00:27:18,246
They have to be burned.

472
00:27:19,320 --> 00:27:20,480
Whoever wants to survive,

473
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:22,720
go ahead and live.

474
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:25,526
If you want to burn, burn me first.

475
00:27:43,100 --> 00:27:43,960
Good.

476
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:44,800
Over there.

477
00:27:46,060 --> 00:27:48,060
ظآزWe workers have strengthظآز

478
00:27:48,300 --> 00:27:52,220
ظآزWorking hard every single dayظآز

479
00:27:52,540 --> 00:27:54,700
ظآزWorking hard every single dayظآز

480
00:27:54,700 --> 00:27:57,060
ظآزWe built towering buildingsظآز

481
00:27:57,060 --> 00:27:58,940
ظآزWe built railways and coal minesظآز

482
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:00,560
Sanyuan.

483
00:28:00,760 --> 00:28:01,600
Where did you go?

484
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:03,200
Let's play.

485
00:28:04,320 --> 00:28:05,160
Same old rules.

486
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:06,800
I'm with Nail.

487
00:28:06,800 --> 00:28:07,960
You're with Guangrong.

488
00:28:08,680 --> 00:28:09,640
Come on, hurry up.

489
00:28:11,800 --> 00:28:12,640
Coming.

490
00:28:15,280 --> 00:28:16,120
So close, so close.

491
00:28:16,920 --> 00:28:18,120
Good, quick, nice.

492
00:28:21,280 --> 00:28:22,120
Good, quick.

493
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:24,000
Nice.

494
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:24,920
Take the shot.

495
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:31,560
He's blocking it.

496
00:28:40,360 --> 00:28:41,440
That jerk.

497
00:28:42,040 --> 00:28:43,360
Useless.

498
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:51,840
That felt great.

499
00:28:52,113 --> 00:28:53,800
I haven't had so much fun
for a long time.

500
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:55,000
Look at that splash.

501
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,880
You're the tricky one;
I had to guard you.

502
00:28:57,520 --> 00:28:59,400
You two work great together.

503
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:00,480
Old partners still click.

504
00:29:00,920 --> 00:29:02,720
One feints; the other goes in.

505
00:29:03,720 --> 00:29:05,640
Guangrong, teach me
to play too sometimes.

506
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:06,973
You can't just teach him.

507
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:12,040
Aunt Hua gave this to you.

508
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:15,546
She said that if you don't get it,
ask me.

509
00:29:15,880 --> 00:29:16,720
What does that mean?

510
00:29:17,280 --> 00:29:18,280
Useless.

511
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:21,520
How can she teach you this?

512
00:29:21,520 --> 00:29:22,360
Sanyuan.

513
00:29:23,320 --> 00:29:24,160
Let's have a drink.

514
00:29:27,480 --> 00:29:28,320
Sure.

515
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:38,800
What are you doing up there?

516
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:42,000
Come up. I'll show you another secret.

517
00:29:44,760 --> 00:29:46,040
Easy. Come on.

518
00:29:49,280 --> 00:29:50,120
Look.

519
00:29:51,360 --> 00:29:52,240
What's she doing?

520
00:29:53,760 --> 00:29:54,600
Dancing.

521
00:29:55,440 --> 00:29:56,640
What kind of dance?

522
00:29:59,160 --> 00:30:00,040
A Western dance.

523
00:30:01,520 --> 00:30:03,640
I think it's called ballet.

524
00:30:04,760 --> 00:30:06,040
I heard

525
00:30:06,040 --> 00:30:08,440
she used to be with the Provincial Song
and Dance Troupe.

526
00:30:09,120 --> 00:30:10,560
I have no idea what she did,

527
00:30:11,360 --> 00:30:12,800
but she got sent here.

528
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:15,040
She's so beautiful.

529
00:30:16,320 --> 00:30:17,160
(Bayi says)

530
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:21,360
(there are lots of secrets
at night in the troupe.)

531
00:30:21,360 --> 00:30:23,840
(He says Shoes Bai is a big bird.)

532
00:30:24,200 --> 00:30:25,880
(Late at night,)

533
00:30:25,880 --> 00:30:27,880
(she dances in secret.)

534
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:30,560
(Huang Zhengjing is a weasel,)

535
00:30:31,160 --> 00:30:32,520
(lurking in the dark)

536
00:30:32,960 --> 00:30:34,280
(to watch the big bird in secret.)

537
00:30:34,560 --> 00:30:35,400
What's he doing?

538
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:07,480
Why does he like ballet so much?

539
00:31:08,900 --> 00:31:09,760
Here.

540
00:31:09,760 --> 00:31:10,600
Here, Sanyuan.

541
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:15,240
How's this liquor?

542
00:31:16,360 --> 00:31:17,200
Good stuff.

543
00:31:17,360 --> 00:31:19,080
Yeah, really good stuff.

544
00:31:19,880 --> 00:31:22,000
Strong, but it doesn't hit too hard.

545
00:31:22,520 --> 00:31:23,520
Next time I come back,

546
00:31:23,520 --> 00:31:24,840
I'll bring you a few more bottles.

547
00:31:27,360 --> 00:31:28,920
Don't you need coupons for this?

548
00:31:29,320 --> 00:31:30,280
I do, of course.

549
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:32,640
But I'm with factory leadership.

550
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:34,120
Our factory is a major one.

551
00:31:34,120 --> 00:31:35,520
The Commerce Bureau helps us out.

552
00:31:35,520 --> 00:31:37,120
A few bottles are no big deal.

553
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:39,400
Your job has its perks.

554
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:41,080
Just a little convenience.

555
00:31:42,080 --> 00:31:43,480
It's not just cigarettes and liquor.

556
00:31:44,040 --> 00:31:46,360
Phoenix, Pigeon bicycles.

557
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:47,480
Shanghai-brand watch.

558
00:31:47,880 --> 00:31:49,320
I can get you anything you want.

559
00:31:50,520 --> 00:31:53,080
Director Huang asked me to buy a watch.

560
00:31:53,080 --> 00:31:54,166
I gave it to him this time.

561
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:56,480
I don't need it.

562
00:31:59,080 --> 00:32:00,400
You don't need it now.

563
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:02,400
But you'll need it when you marry.

564
00:32:03,440 --> 00:32:05,160
A bike, a watch,

565
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:06,680
a sewing machine, and a radio.

566
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:08,880
You must have the Three Turns
and One Sound.

567
00:32:10,040 --> 00:32:11,880
You're not young and still single.

568
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:13,080
I'm worried for you.

569
00:32:14,400 --> 00:32:16,960
I'm the single one. Why are you worried?

570
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:19,840
You're probably the only one left

571
00:32:21,013 --> 00:32:22,200
who worries about my marriage

572
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:23,760
and helps set me up with a wife.

573
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:27,160
You even want that full set for me.

574
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:32,160
I should thank you
on behalf of my late parents.

575
00:32:46,920 --> 00:32:47,760
Give it here.

576
00:33:35,920 --> 00:33:37,480
Why are they burning it?

577
00:33:56,720 --> 00:33:57,560
What are you doing?

578
00:33:58,720 --> 00:33:59,640
Didn't I tell you?

579
00:34:00,560 --> 00:34:01,760
Burn me if you have to.

580
00:34:02,800 --> 00:34:03,640
Trying to scare me?

581
00:34:04,280 --> 00:34:05,120
If you want to die,

582
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:06,920
choose one

583
00:34:07,520 --> 00:34:08,360
of the two furnaces.

584
00:34:09,640 --> 00:34:11,600
Zhou, burn him first.

585
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:14,600
Then burn me.

586
00:34:19,920 --> 00:34:20,760
This is bad.

587
00:34:21,520 --> 00:34:23,000
They pried the furnace open.

588
00:34:23,560 --> 00:34:25,120
Don't burn through my dad's pot.

589
00:34:26,840 --> 00:34:28,440
I have a place for them. Go.

590
00:34:30,720 --> 00:34:31,560
Go, now.

591
00:34:32,080 --> 00:34:32,920
Hurry.

592
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:01,760
(Back then,)

593
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:05,080
(Yi Qing'e had no idea
what the old opera was.)

594
00:35:05,560 --> 00:35:06,760
(She understood even less)

595
00:35:07,080 --> 00:35:09,560
(how the gatekeeper, troupe sweeper,)

596
00:35:09,560 --> 00:35:10,880
(and the cook)

597
00:35:11,040 --> 00:35:13,040
(could value a few trunks)

598
00:35:13,040 --> 00:35:15,160
(more than their lives.)

599
00:35:16,240 --> 00:35:18,640
(During those silent years
for the old opera,)

600
00:35:18,640 --> 00:35:20,680
(they were sealed away in boxes
in the storeroom,)

601
00:35:20,880 --> 00:35:23,320
(just like these opera costumes,)

602
00:35:24,160 --> 00:35:27,520
(and now, even the boxes
won't hold them.)

603
00:35:28,520 --> 00:35:31,680
(Yi Qing'e watched them
hiding away these old clothes)

604
00:35:31,680 --> 00:35:33,600
(like rats moving.)

605
00:35:33,960 --> 00:35:35,760
(She was confused,)

606
00:35:36,880 --> 00:35:38,160
(but she didn't know)

607
00:35:38,880 --> 00:35:40,520
(that what these people were hiding)

608
00:35:41,320 --> 00:35:44,040
(was more than a few old clothes;)

609
00:35:44,440 --> 00:35:49,080
(it was hope
for the old Qinqiang opera.)

610
00:35:51,160 --> 00:35:52,480
Watch your step.

611
00:35:52,480 --> 00:35:53,360
Be careful.

612
00:35:56,200 --> 00:35:57,040
Watch out.

613
00:35:57,720 --> 00:35:58,760
Careful, careful.

614
00:36:09,120 --> 00:36:10,120
At our factory,

615
00:36:10,800 --> 00:36:12,160
there was an engineer.

616
00:36:13,520 --> 00:36:16,400
He was in every political campaign.

617
00:36:17,480 --> 00:36:18,720
He wore

618
00:36:19,760 --> 00:36:20,880
all the labels.

619
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:23,160
He went through

620
00:36:24,320 --> 00:36:25,160
humiliation parade,

621
00:36:25,820 --> 00:36:27,099
struggle session, and detention.

622
00:36:27,560 --> 00:36:29,240
Still, they couldn't break him.

623
00:36:29,920 --> 00:36:31,400
He claimed he was

624
00:36:33,920 --> 00:36:35,080
a campaign veteran.

625
00:36:38,760 --> 00:36:41,480
A few days after his release,
he went back to the factory.

626
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:43,360
One day,

627
00:36:44,640 --> 00:36:45,840
he hung himself.

628
00:36:51,240 --> 00:36:52,400
Do you know why?

629
00:36:56,240 --> 00:36:57,080
Why?

630
00:36:58,320 --> 00:36:59,160
He found out

631
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:01,000
that at home,

632
00:37:01,480 --> 00:37:03,240
there was another label waiting for him.

633
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:08,520
None of the other labels
matched that one.

634
00:37:10,960 --> 00:37:13,120
His dignity as a man

635
00:37:14,160 --> 00:37:15,000
was gone.

636
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:17,760
He couldn't go on.

637
00:37:19,720 --> 00:37:20,560
How could he?

638
00:37:43,160 --> 00:37:44,000
It was all gone.

639
00:37:44,480 --> 00:37:45,320
Alright.

640
00:37:45,760 --> 00:37:46,600
Then let's not drink.

641
00:37:49,600 --> 00:37:50,600
Where's your liquor?

642
00:37:51,320 --> 00:37:52,160
Bring it here.

643
00:38:06,280 --> 00:38:07,120
Bye.

644
00:38:15,360 --> 00:38:16,200
Laidi.

645
00:38:18,320 --> 00:38:19,160
Come here.

646
00:38:32,320 --> 00:38:33,160
Stop drinking.

647
00:38:33,720 --> 00:38:34,560
Let's stop drinking.

648
00:38:35,080 --> 00:38:35,960
That's enough.

649
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:36,960
Alright, enough.

650
00:38:40,220 --> 00:38:41,080
Yeah, yeah.

651
00:38:41,080 --> 00:38:42,060
You stop. I'll drink.

652
00:38:42,060 --> 00:38:42,940
I'll drink.

653
00:38:45,360 --> 00:38:46,200
Why?

654
00:38:47,160 --> 00:38:49,120
I'm single. I'll be fine drunk.

655
00:38:49,120 --> 00:38:50,440
I'm single too.

656
00:38:50,960 --> 00:38:52,840
I'm a married single guy.

657
00:38:53,560 --> 00:38:54,400
Come on.

658
00:38:58,320 --> 00:38:59,160
They all say

659
00:39:00,080 --> 00:39:02,400
parting sweetens love.

660
00:39:05,120 --> 00:39:06,560
I came back all excited,

661
00:39:06,560 --> 00:39:08,480
but my wife feels like a stranger.

662
00:39:09,960 --> 00:39:10,920
Tell me why.

663
00:39:13,800 --> 00:39:14,880
You're drunk.

664
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:17,160
I'm perfectly sober.

665
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:25,480
In my house,

666
00:39:26,080 --> 00:39:28,240
the other pillow belongs to whom?

667
00:39:30,440 --> 00:39:31,840
My niece.

668
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:34,560
She's too old to sleep

669
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:35,520
with me here.

670
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:37,360
Your niece?

671
00:39:38,480 --> 00:39:39,560
Fine.

672
00:39:45,040 --> 00:39:45,920
Which one do you like?

673
00:39:46,880 --> 00:39:47,920
Both.

674
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:49,480
You can only pick one.

675
00:39:52,040 --> 00:39:53,360
Alright, this is enough.

676
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:54,440
Go and get some sleep.

677
00:39:55,600 --> 00:39:57,040
What are you doing?

678
00:39:57,680 --> 00:39:59,160
If you plan to stay alone,

679
00:39:59,760 --> 00:40:01,720
I'll hit you every time I get back,

680
00:40:02,360 --> 00:40:03,840
till the day you get married.

681
00:40:04,520 --> 00:40:06,480
Who do you think you are?
None of your business.

682
00:40:09,400 --> 00:40:10,240
Yeah, yeah.

683
00:40:10,960 --> 00:40:12,400
Go back to sleep.

684
00:40:21,840 --> 00:40:22,880
Come on, get up there.

685
00:40:22,880 --> 00:40:24,920
The steps. Get up.

686
00:40:26,680 --> 00:40:27,520
Go on.

687
00:40:28,680 --> 00:40:29,520
Go.

688
00:40:29,640 --> 00:40:30,480
Up.

689
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:32,840
Here, here.

690
00:40:48,080 --> 00:40:48,920
Hua Caixiang.

691
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:50,200
Hua Caixiang?

692
00:40:53,400 --> 00:40:54,720
Laidi, Laidi.

693
00:40:54,720 --> 00:40:56,400
What is it? Why are you yowling?

694
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:57,640
What is it?

695
00:40:57,840 --> 00:40:58,980
I'll bring her back to sleep.

696
00:40:59,280 --> 00:41:00,120
She's asleep.

697
00:41:00,200 --> 00:41:01,120
If she's sleeping here,

698
00:41:02,520 --> 00:41:03,893
where's Zhang Guangrong sleeping?

699
00:41:04,320 --> 00:41:05,560
He can crash wherever he wants.

700
00:41:07,320 --> 00:41:08,360
He's totally wasted.

701
00:41:10,040 --> 00:41:11,800
Whoever got him drunk can deal with it.

702
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:13,400
How can I handle that?

703
00:41:15,440 --> 00:41:16,280
Just open the door.

704
00:41:17,840 --> 00:41:19,160
Open up and get him inside.

705
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:21,720
Get lost.

706
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

707
00:43:09,930 --> 00:43:11,060
This trainee class

708
00:43:11,060 --> 00:43:12,470
has to be run like the military.

709
00:43:12,470 --> 00:43:13,680
Let Laidi sleep next to you.

710
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:15,680
But Yu Liping and Zhou Yuzhi
want to sleep next to me.

711
00:43:15,680 --> 00:43:17,460
We've been together since nursery.

712
00:43:17,460 --> 00:43:19,150
Why weren't you together before birth?

713
00:43:19,150 --> 00:43:20,440
Perform well in opera.

714
00:43:20,770 --> 00:43:21,840
Be the lead.

715
00:43:21,840 --> 00:43:23,280
Have them play bit parts for you.

716
00:43:23,280 --> 00:43:24,270
What is it?

717
00:43:25,490 --> 00:43:27,360
(A Happy Family)
Take that photo off the cabinet.

718
00:43:27,360 --> 00:43:28,310
Why?

719
00:43:28,310 --> 00:43:29,480
Take it down right now.

720
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
ظآزWhen I woke up and turned backظآز

721
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
ظآزI wasn't sure where to goظآز

722
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
ظآزWe met and brushed pastظآز

723
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
ظآزYour shadow drifted out of sightظآز

724
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
ظآزThe stove fire blazed in my dreamظآز

725
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
ظآزLit up the tracks of pearly tearsظآز

726
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
ظآزIn my dream, water sleeves flewظآز

727
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
ظآزHiding a lifetime of loveظآز

728
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
ظآزThe Qinling Mountains
crossed the stageظآز

729
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
ظآزSpring water brewed strong wineظآز

730
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
ظآزSheep moved through the valleyظآز

731
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
ظآزIt felt like a promise
from another lifeظآز

732
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
ظآزWhen I woke up and turned backظآز

733
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
ظآزI wasn't sure where to goظآز

734
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
ظآزIf I chose again, I'd still roamظآز

735
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
ظآزAll over this sunlit plateauظآز

736
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
ظآزThe dream ends; the curtain fallsظآز

737
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
ظآزMoonlight washes off this stage makeupظآز

738
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
ظآزThe one in the mirror wears gray hairظآز

739
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
ظآزAlready sang all my joy and sorrowظآز

740
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
ظآزAlready shouted across Qinchuan Plainظآز
